                <note rend="inline" type="source">462.00 R 29/500: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wallace</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-03-09T16:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 9, 1921—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>136. Following for Boyden.</p>
                <p>Your telegram B–421. It is desired that you remain in Paris pending an
                    opportunity for consideration of what steps, if any, <pb facs="0136" n="12"
                        xml:id="pg_12"/> should be taken in interest of this Government respecting
                    activities of Reparation Commission. Meanwhile, without in any way committing
                    this Government, you may unofficially obtain and report any information of
                    interest to this Government. Department would appreciate your suggestions as to
                    how above may best be accomplished.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
